Relationships would be awesome:<p><pre><code>  .col1 {
      height: {col2.height};
  }
</code></pre>
Basically what people do with JavaScript, but built-in. Implementation-wise, I don't think it would be very difficult to make two block-level elements abide by each other's box model (determine height of .col1 as if it were .col2's parent).<p>This would have very good consequences for user-customizable pages as well.
